\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}m(m-1)\ldots(m-r+1)=\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}\frac{m!}{(m-r)!};\quad r=1,2,\ldots
\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}m(m-1)\ldots(m-r+1)=\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}\frac{m(m-1)\ldots[m-(r-1)][m-(r-2)]\ldots(3)(2)(1)}{[m-(r-2)]\ldots(3)(2)(1)}=\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}\frac{m!}{[m-(r-2)]!}
\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}m(m-1)\ldots(m-r+1)=\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}\frac{m(m-1)\ldots[m-(r-1)][m-(r-2)]\ldots(3)(2)(1)}{[m-(r-2)]\ldots(3)(2)(1)}.
